# Pricing trust rules

> Terminology definitions: [`non-negotiable-rules.mdc`](./non-negotiable-rules.mdc) § Terminology policy.
> Formula and karat constants: [`gold-pricing-integrity.mdc`](./gold-pricing-integrity.mdc).

- Reference prices are not retail quotes.
- Karat calculations must remain internally consistent (`src/config/karats.js`, `src/config/constants.js`).
- `Live` must only be used for truly live data — see terminology policy.
- `Cached`, `delayed`, and `updated` labels must be truthful.
- Any wording that increases certainty must be reviewed carefully.
- Never strip freshness labels, disclaimers, or methodology links to “look cleaner.”
- Calculator output is always a reference estimate; disclose making charges, VAT, and that shops may charge differently.
